<p>3. SEVERE & COMMON ADVERSE EFFECTS (NON-EXHAUSTIVE)

IMPORTANT: The following adverse effects are reported, observed in testing, or reasonably foreseeable. They range from mild to life-threatening. This list is non-exhaustive. Seek immediate medical attention for any severe symptoms.

Common / Moderate (may occur in many users):

Nausea, vomiting, diarrhea, abdominal pain.

Headache, dizziness, lightheadedness, vertigo.

Rapid or irregular heartbeat (palpitations).

Insomnia, agitation, nervousness, restlessness.

Elevated blood pressure.

Unexplained sweating or chills.

Mild to severe allergic reactions (rash, itching, hives).

Severe / Potentially Life-Threatening (reported or possible):

Cardiac arrhythmia, heart attack (myocardial infarction), or cardiac arrest.

Stroke, transient ischemic attack, or other cerebrovascular events.

Severe hypertension or hypertensive crisis requiring emergency care.

Seizures, convulsions, loss of consciousness.

Acute liver injury or liver failure. Indicators include severe abdominal pain, jaundice, dark urine, pale stools.

Acute kidney injury or renal failure, possibly requiring dialysis.

Severe respiratory distress, pulmonary edema, or acute shortness of breath.

Thrombotic events (blood clots), deep vein thrombosis, pulmonary embolism.

Hemorrhagic events or abnormal bleeding.

Psychosis, suicidal ideation, violent behavior, or severe mood disturbance.

Permanent neurological damage, neuropathy, motor impairment.

Severe skin reactions including Stevens–Johnson syndrome or toxic epidermal necrolysis.

Death. </p>
